        "en": "Per DART-filed consolidated financial statements, LG Electronics reported full-year 2025 revenue of 89.2 trillion won (+1.7% YoY)—a company all-time record—but operating profit fell sharply to 2.5 trillion won, down 27.5% YoY, as demand recovery delays in TVs and display products, elevated marketing spend amid intensifying competition, and voluntary retirement charges combined to suppress earnings; the Q4 2025 operating loss of 109.4 billion won underscored the severity of the year-end deterioration. Net profit for 2025 surged 106.4% YoY to 1.2 trillion won, driven significantly by non-operating items including asset disposal gains rather than underlying operating improvement. A decisive reversal materialized in Q1 2026: DART-confirmed consolidated revenue reached 23.7 trillion won (+4.3% YoY), a first-quarter all-time record, while operating profit of 1.7 trillion won (+32.9% YoY) beat market consensus by 21.1%, constituting a clear earnings surprise. Operating margin expanded to 7.1%, and net profit grew 14.8% YoY to 1.0 trillion won. By segment, HS posted a record quarterly revenue and the combined HS and VS revenue crossed 10 trillion won for the first time ever; the ES division led all segments with an 8.8% operating margin, cementing its status as a key growth engine. The MS division staged a notable profitability recovery through premium TV sales growth and cost rationalization, while VS achieved a record quarterly result underpinned by its robust order backlog. On the stock, shares hit back-to-back upper-limit closes on May 29 and June 1, 2026, and as of June 4, 2026 trade at 392,500 won (+3.15%) with a market capitalization of 63.9 trillion won—driven by NVIDIA CEO Jensen Huang's planned Korea visit and anticipated discussions with LG Group Chairman Koo Kwang-mo on physical AI and robotics collaboration."
